===Origins===
To facilitate his deicidal crusade, the dark god [[Knull (Earth-616)|Knull]] created a species of [[Symbiotes|amorphous symbiotic predators]] from the "living abyss", using them to conquer planets and consume entire civilizations.{{r|Venom Vol 4 4}} Establishing himself as the nexus of his creations' hivemind, Knull created a [[Klyntar (Location)|throneworld]] out of living abyss and began establishing an empire of darkness and death across the nascent cosmos.{{r|Silver Surfer: Black Vol 1 1|5}}

At one point thousands of years in the past, the Symbiote Hive attempted to conquer the [[Microverse]] in order to assimilate the [[Glossary:Enigma Force|Enigma Force]], hoping to become able to infest entire planets. The symbiotes' touch proved caustic to the minuscule dimension and its inhabitants, and nearly wound up destroying it and all existence; but they were repelled by the [[Redeemer (Microverse) (Earth-616)|Enigma Force's avatar]].{{r|Venom Vol 2 26|27}}{{r|Scarlet Spider Vol 2 11}}

[[File:Knull Marvel Tales Vol 1 1 Unknown Comic Books Exclusive Virgin Variant.jpg|thumb|left|Knull's dark army]]
Knull's control over the symbiotes was severed in a battle between [[Grendel (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|one of his symbiote-dragons]] and [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]]. Being disconnected from Knull caused the symbiote dragons to unravel into countless individual symbiotes, which sought out hosts to stabilize themselves. The symbiotes who had bonded to noble and kind-hearted hosts poisoned the Hive-Mind with the Light, leading to the symbiotes rebelling against Knull and imprisoning him at the core of the symbiote throneworld -- renaming it and themselves "Klyntar" after the symbiote word for prison.{{r|Venom Vol 4 4}} 

===Post-Knull Empire===
Ashamed of their dark past, the symbiotes of Klyntar desired to spread and maintain peace throughout the Cosmos by seeking out worthy hosts from various species in order to create an organization of noble warriors, the [[Agents of the Cosmos (Earth-616)|Agents of the Cosmos]].{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 3 23}} However, many of the symbiotes — including the one who would later become [[Venom (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Venom]] — were bonded to unworthy hosts, "corrupting" them with hatred, rage, and ravenous predatory hunger.{{r|Venom Vol 1 158}} These "corrupted" symbiotes were cast out of the Symbiotes hive-mind,{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 3 23}} which took to forcibly cleansing those it captured and executing those who resisted or relapsed.{{r|Venom: Space Knight Vol 1 10}}

[[File:Hive (Symbiotes) (Earth-616) from Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 430.png|thumb|left|Symbiote Imperium]]
Despite being cut off from the hive-mind, the corrupted symbiotes formed into a loosely-organized spacefaring empire and resumed conquering planets, spreading what the Symbiotes hive-mind claimed was misinformation about their species.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 3 23}}{{r|Venom: Space Knight Vol 1 8}} While some of the corrupted symbiotes took to overwhelming their hosts with bloodlust and corrupting them;{{r|Venom: Space Knight Vol 1 8}}{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 118|119}}{{r|Venom Vol 2 26}} the vast majority came to see their hosts as nothing more than chattel and developed the practice of seizing control of their bodies; parasitically draining their vitality, phenethylamine, adrenaline, and other body fluids until they expired; and devouring their flesh before seeking out new hosts to repeat the process.{{r|Venom Super Special Vol 1 1}}{{r|Spider-Man and the X-Men Vol 1 5}} As a result, the corrupted symbiotes caused their species as a whole to become once-again feared as one of the galaxy's apex predators, their hosts treated with fear and mistrust.{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 3 14}} 

At some point in the past, Joot, one of the worlds conquered by the Symbiote Hive, was devoured by Galactus, amplifying the symbiotes' instinctual fear and hatred towards the cosmic entity and his herald, the Silver Surfer.{{r|Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 430|431}}

===Modern Times===
The arms dealer [[Haze Mancer (Earth-616)|Haze Mancer]] was an unwitting ally of the Hive, abducting uncorrupted symbiotes from Klyntar, weaponizing them with chemicals that corrupted them by amplifying their aggression and bloodlust, and selling them to space-pirates and warlords.{{r|X-Men: Blue Vol 1 21}}{{r|Venom Vol 1 162}}

[[Venom (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|The symbiote that would become known as "Venom"]] was once a member of the Hive, having been a member of the [[Agents of the Cosmos (Earth-616)|Agents of the Cosmos]] before being corrupted by its original host.{{r|Venom: Space Knight Vol 1 8}} However, it was deemed aberrant for its desire to protect its hosts, and was imprisoned to prevent it from contaminating the Hive with like-minded spawn.{{r|Venom Super Special Vol 1 1}} The Venom symbiote was later unwittingly freed by Spider-Man, who brought it to Earth where it eventually reproduced - having come to consider humanity its Hive.{{r|Venom Vol 4 20}} Despite the Venom symbiote's increasing corruption and malevolence, neither it nor [[Carnage (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|its nihilistic and bloodthirsty spawn]] made any deliberate attempt to contact or rejoin the Symbiote Hive.

