The Symbiote Hive [[Planet of the Symbiotes (Event)|once attempted to conquer Earth]], having been unintentionally summoned by the Venom symbiote, before being routed by Spider-Man, his clone the Scarlet Spider, Venom, and Carnage. Almost all of the invading symbiotes committed suicide after Venom unleashed a scream of despair,{{r|Web of Spider-Man Super Special Vol 1 1}} and most of the surviving invaders were eaten by a [[Xenophage]];{{r|Venom: The Hunted Vol 1 1|3}} though one tried to get revenge on the "race traitor" Venom and was killed when its host, [[Rune (Earth-93060)|Rune]], managed to break free of its control and devour it.{{r|Rune vs. Venom Vol 1 1}}

At some point, a symbiote called [[Zzzxx (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Zzzxx]] attacked the [[Shi'ar Empire]], but was captured and turned into a living weapon.{{r|X-Men: Kingbreaker Vol 1 2}} Members of the Hive tricked a swarm of [[Brood (Race)|Brood]] into becoming their hosts and attacked the [[Sentient World Observation and Response Department (Earth-616)|S.W.O.R.D.]] space station in an attempt to lay claim to [[Deathbird's Child (Earth-616)|the unborn child of Deathbird]] while plotting to use his power to facilitate their conquest of the galaxy, but were repelled by members of the X-Men and Spider-Man.{{r|Spider-Man and the X-Men Vol 1 5}}

====Return of Knull and a new King in Black====
After [[Cletus Kasady (Earth-616)|Carnage]]'s resurrection as a result of being bonded to [[Carnage IV (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|a piece]] of the [[Grendel (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Grendel symbiote]], he began hunting down previous symbiote hosts in order to extract their codices - the remnants of symbiotes in a host's body - and free Knull.{{r|Web of Venom: Carnage Born Vol 1 1}} He succeeded in his mission, making Venom kill him and forcibly making the Venom symbiote assimilate the Grendel symbiote and the codices, freeing Knull. Upon awakening, Knull destroyed [[Klyntar (Location)|Klyntar]] and merged its constituent symbiotes into a fleet of [[Symbiote Dragons]], resuming his conquest to destroy the cosmos.{{r|Absolute Carnage Vol 1 5}}

[[File:Edward Brock (Earth-616) and Venom (Symbiote) (Earth-616) from King in Black Vol 1 5 001.jpg|thumb|New King in Black]]
Under Knull's command, the Symbiote Hive decimated entire worlds en route to Earth.{{r|Incoming Vol 1 1}}{{r|Guardians of the Galaxy Vol 6 8}}{{r|Web of Venom: Empyre's End Vol 1 1}}{{r|S.W.O.R.D. Vol 2 3}} However, following Knull's defeat they recognized Eddie Brock as the new King in Black, making him the nexus of the Hive-Mind.{{r|King in Black Vol 1 5}} Eddie's first act was to sentence the Carnage symbiote - which was being piloted by Cletus Kasady's codex - to execution,{{r|Carnage: Black, White & Blood Vol 1 2}} but a piece of the symbiote survived and made its way back to New York.{{r|Extreme Carnage Alpha Vol 1 1}} 

Over the next few months, Eddie granted the symbiotes free will - only remote-piloting them if they allowed him to - but tasked them with helping repair the damage they had caused under Knull's control and with maintaining peace across the cosmos. Some symbiotes chose to remain on Earth and take new hosts, but found themselves the target of anti-extraterrestrial hatred and hunted by the [[Friends of Humanity (Earth-616)|Friends of Humanity]] and [[Alchemax (Earth-616)|Alchemax]]'s [[Guardsmen (Alchemax) (Earth-616)|Guardsmen]].{{r|Venom Vol 4 35}} In the meantime, Carnage began using the power Knull had granted him to corrupt other symbiotes, intending to establish [[Carnage's Hive (Earth-616)|a rival Hive]] with himself as the deified nexus and ultimately dethrone Eddie.{{r|Extreme Carnage Alpha Vol 1 1}}{{r|Extreme Carnage: Scream Vol 1 1}}
