| Trivia                  = * The timeline of the Symbiote Hive is inconsistently depicted within the comics. {{cl|Thor: God of Thunder Vol 1 6}} establishes that [[Gorr (God Butcher) (Earth-616)|Gorr]] stealing [[All-Black (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|All-Black]] from [[Knull (Earth-616)|Knull]] happened ~3000 years ago (which is what the appendix at the end of {{cl|King in Black Vol 1 1}} goes with), and {{cl|Venom Vol 4 4}} reveals Knull created the [[Symbiotes]] ~100 years after losing All-Black; but {{cl|Venom Vol 4 3}}, ''[[Silver Surfer: Black Vol 1|Silver Surfer: Black]]'', [[Scream: Curse of Carnage Vol 1|Scream: Curse of Carnage]], and [[Savage Avengers Vol 1|Savage Avengers]] show him having created the symbiotes and [[Symbiote Dragons|symbiote-dragons]] billions of years in the past, while he still had All-Black. ''Venom'' #4 further establishes that Knull only lost control of the Symbiote Hive in the 6th century CE, which is when symbiotes first arrived on Earth in the form of the [[Grendel (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Grendel]] (and [[Big Mother (Symbiote) (Earth-616)|Big Mother]] according to ''Scream: Curse of Carnage''). {{cl|Free Comic Book Day Vol 2020 Spider-Man/Venom}} has Eddie state that Knull was imprisoned by the symbiotes billions of years ago; while {{cl|Carnage: Black, White & Blood Vol 1 1}} (assuming [[Lucius Marius (Earth-616)|Lucius Marius]] isn't a figment of Cletus' twisted imagination) shows a symbiote being present on Earth during the time of the [[Roman Empire]], and ''Savage Avengers'' shows a symbiote being present on Earth in the [[Hyborian Age]] - roughly 10 000 years before present.
